  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7094 sitting just below the massive 7100 gamma wall (12.2B), dealers are positioned to sell any push higher into that level, creating strong resistance. The PIN regime with 105B total GEX confirms dealers are long gamma and will provide stabilizing flows - selling the current -0.6% dip and capping upside momentum near 7100. Watch for mean reversion back toward 7100 with the next major resistance at 7200 (7.3B) if we break above, while downside acceleration would only emerge below the 6872 flip level.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to grind back up toward 7100 but struggle to break meaningfully higher.",
